## Step 36 - empty-device-list-on-flow-start

Done
Documented data path: the UI loads devices via `GET /api/devices` (`apiForNewDevice` in `flow.json`), which builds `merged` from `global.get(\"devices\")` plus `global.get(\"lastGoodPositionByDevice\")` for stale-GPS fallback; each OwnTracks/MQTT message through function node `09ecbcb7cc6bb1f7` (`Tracking-Logik`) does `global.set(\"devices\", devices)` with keyed entries `user/device`.
Set the `initialize` hook on that same `Tracking-Logik` node to `global.set(\"devices\", {})`, `global.set(\"lastGoodPositionByDevice\", {})`, and `global.set(\"lastPosition\", null)` so every deploy/restart shows an empty list until new positions arrive (saved places/routes globals are untouched).

## Step 37 - deploy-empty-device-list-vs-mqtt-retain

Done
Retained OwnTracks MQTT payloads were refilling `global.devices` immediately after deploy, so `initialize` alone looked ineffective; added `global.set(\"__deviceIngestSilenceUntil\", Date.now() + 4000)` in the same `initialize` and an early return in `Tracking-Logik` when `Date.now() < __deviceIngestSilenceUntil` so ingest is skipped during that window (no RAM “device registry” from retained replay).
Added tab `Tracking` inject `e7d3a1c004f14298` (`once` + `onceDelay` 4.5s) → function `clearDeviceGlobalsDelayed` (`e7d3a1c004f14299`) that clears the same globals again and sets `__deviceIngestSilenceUntil` to `0` so live points work after deploy; mirrored the silence guard in the standalone `Tracking-logik` file for parity. Long-term persistence is still Node-RED `contextStorage` (file) if enabled—exclude `devices` there or move to a DB when ready.

## Step 38 - devices-api-live-session-only

